<text top="109" left="108" width="706" height="18" font="0">Lucian  Parisi  develops  software  for  spatial  audio,  on-device  inference,  and  interactive  media. </text>
<text top="130" left="108" width="706" height="18" font="0">His  experience  spans industry engineering, open-source development, immersive installations, </text>
<text top="152" left="108" width="316" height="18" font="0">audio engineering and academic research. </text>
<text top="174" left="108" width="5" height="18" font="0"> </text>
<text top="196" left="108" width="291" height="18" font="0">Résumé · GitHub · Multimedia Portfolio </text>
<text top="218" left="108" width="5" height="18" font="0"> </text>
<text top="239" left="108" width="706" height="18" font="0">Currently  developing  secure,  on-device  speech  systems  at  Qualcomm; previously built spatial </text>
<text top="261" left="108" width="601" height="18" font="0">audio and immersive graphics infrastructure with the AlloSphere Research Group. </text>
<text top="314" left="108" width="370" height="34" font="1">Open Source Spatial Audio </text>
<text top="362" left="108" width="124" height="18" font="0">CULT DSP is an<a href="https://github.com/Cult-DSP"> </a></text>
<text top="362" left="232" width="92" height="18" font="2"><a href="https://github.com/Cult-DSP">open-source</a></text>
<text top="362" left="324" width="449" height="18" font="0"><a href="https://github.com/Cult-DSP"> </a>spatial audio ecosystem designed to make immersive media </text>
<text top="384" left="108" width="617" height="18" font="0">more portable across formats, software environments, and loudspeaker systems. Its </text>
<text top="405" left="108" width="670" height="18" font="0">interconnected tools support the full workflow from transcoding and scene representation to </text>
<text top="427" left="108" width="697" height="18" font="0">authoring, integration, and playback. The toolchain and its applications have been presented at </text>
<text top="449" left="108" width="28" height="18" font="0">the </text>
<text top="449" left="136" width="176" height="18" font="2"><a href="https://lac2026.sciencesconf.org/723182/document">Linux Audio Conference</a></text>
<text top="449" left="311" width="274" height="18" font="0"> and the Audio Engineering Society’s<a href="https://aes.org/publications/elibrary-page/?id=23337"> </a></text>
<text top="449" left="585" width="206" height="18" font="2"><a href="https://aes.org/publications/elibrary-page/?id=23337">immersive audio conference</a></text>
<text top="449" left="791" width="9" height="18" font="0">. </text>
<text top="495" left="108" width="126" height="23" font="3">Spatial Root  </text>
<text top="529" left="108" width="686" height="18" font="0">A C++ spatial audio engine for real-time and offline playback of Atmos/ADM-based immersive </text>
<text top="550" left="108" width="386" height="18" font="0">audio on arbitrary multichannel loudspeaker layouts. </text>
<text top="596" left="108" width="68" height="23" font="3">LUSID </text>
<text top="630" left="108" width="674" height="18" font="0">A lightweight JSON scene format for representing moving audio objects, speaker beds, LFE </text>
<text top="652" left="108" width="515" height="18" font="0">content, and time-varying metadata across spatial-media applications. </text>
<text top="698" left="108" width="176" height="23" font="3">CULT Transcoder  </text>
<text top="731" left="108" width="656" height="18" font="0">A C++ tool that converts Atmos/ADM and BW64 audio into LUSID scenes and can author </text>
<text top="753" left="108" width="409" height="18" font="0">LUSID packages back into ADM-compatible audio files. </text>
<text top="799" left="108" width="125" height="23" font="3">Spatial Seed </text>
<text top="833" left="108" width="664" height="18" font="0">An early-development procedural authoring system that uses music information retrieval to </text>
<text top="855" left="108" width="522" height="18" font="0">generate object placement and movement for immersive audio scenes. </text>
<text top="901" left="108" width="255" height="23" font="3">Implementation Prototypes </text>
<text top="934" left="108" width="683" height="18" font="0">A collection of experimental hosts and integrations that demonstrate the CULT DSP toolchain </text>
<text top="956" left="108" width="562" height="18" font="0">across AlloLib, Unreal Engine, web, and networked spatial-media workflows. </text>
<text top="978" left="108" width="5" height="18" font="0"> </text>
<text top="1000" left="108" width="5" height="18" font="0"> </text>
</page>
